    "The study identified hundreds of species based on a newly established fossil dataset called the 'bivalve and brachiopod fossil image dataset' (BBFID) (Sun et al. 2023) which compiled data from other publications.",
    "Moreover, the authors establish a distinctive boundary between the morphological feature points of bivalves and brachiopods in feature distribution maps.",
    "The imbalanced data contributions to the training data from different publications affect the model's generalization ability, and the lack of labels for specific fossil groups could negatively impact identification accuracy.",
    "Wang et al. (2022) explore the use of a Transpose Convolutional Neural Network (TCNN) for brachiopod fossil classification (5 species).",
    "TCNN is a CNN variant designed to handle sequence data effectively and is often used in tasks that involve temporal dependencies."
